1402.desc: You gaze into the room and hundreds of skulls gaze coldly back at you. They're set in niches in the walls in a checkerboard pattern, each skull bearing a half-melted candle on its head. The grinning bones stare vacantly into the room.
1402.name: Room full of Skulls

1417.desc: A shattered crate, with many of its pieces lying around it.
1417.name: Broken Crate

1425.desc: A ration, good for your everyday adventures!
1425.name: Rations

1426.desc: An ornate looking door, or at least it would have been long ago. Now just a shell of its former self, with decorations long ago faded
1426.name: Ornate Door

1436.desc: This room is hung with hundreds of dusty tapestries. All show signs of wear: moth holes, scorch marks, dark stains, and the damage of years of neglect. They hang on all the walls and hang from the ceiling to brush against the floor.
1436.name: Room

1438.desc: The only sounds you hear in this room are the echos of your footsteps, as the sound bounces back from unseen walls in the distance. The darkness in this room is almost suffocating as the pitch blackness seem to dim whatever lights might be here.
1438.name: Cavern

1440.desc: A chill crawls up your spine and out over your skin as you look upon this room. The carvings on the wall are magnificent, a symphony in stonework -- but given the themes represented, it might be better described as a requiem. Scenes of death, both violent and peaceful, appear on every wall framed by grinning skeletons and ghoulish forms in ragged cloaks.
1440.name: Room of Requiem

1441.desc: The only sounds you hear in this room are the echos of your footsteps, as the sound bounces back from unseen walls in the distance. The darkness in this room is almost suffocating as the pitch blackness seem to dim whatever lights might be here.
1441.name: Cavern

1442.desc: You open the door to confront a room of odd pillars. Water rushes down from several holes in the ceiling and falls through similar holes in the floor, flowing down to some unknown depth.
1442.name: Room

1455.desc: A crate with many cracks around it.
1455.name: Broken Crate

1500.desc: A chill wind blows against you as you enter the room. Beyond it, you see that the floor and ceiling are nothing but iron grates. Above and below the grates the walls extend up and down with no true ceiling or floor within your range of vision. It's as though the chamber is a bridge through the shaft of a great well. Standing on the edge of this shaft, you feel a chill wind pass down it and over your shoulder into the hall beyond.
1500.name: Room
